	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 16th 1:18 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Begin Rant<br><br>I don't rant very often but I am waiting for my lunch and being hungry makes me grouchy.<br><br>The new patch with all the recipes add lots of great items for everyone except rogues.&nbsp;&nbsp;All rogues seem to have gotten was a half way decent set of newbie armor.  Higher level melee types got new player crafted armor.  Casters got new player crafted gear.  We rogues seem to have gotten nothing of any value.  We did get a vague message about looking into revamping poisons but with no specifics as to what was being addressed.  <br><br>Personally, I am tired of being passed over for groups in favor of other classes (unless the dungeon requires a lock picked).  We don't have the HP to tank.  We don't have any useful magic. Poison is too impractical and expensive to use on a regular basis.  We DO help bring MOBs down faster which saves the group injuries and mana but no one seems to care about that!  Instead we get dumped on for being able to pick pockets and accussed of stealing from party treasure (even if we didn't).<br><br>Instill Doubt only works about a third of the time (even at my skill of 170).  This makes it almost useless for Fear Kiting.<br><br>I love casters &lt;not&gt; who think they are doing me a favor casting a buff or DS on me when I am hidden (breaking my hide too soon).<br><br>I wish we had more skills and items that would allow us to solo more.  I love Rogues as a class but in order to work as stealthy killers, as we were meant to do, we need to be able work efficiently without the assistance of others.  Look at bards and necros. They only group when they feel like it.  If rogues as a class are so undesired or unappreciated then VI needs to fix the rogue class so it can function more independently.  VI needs to provide player made gear for the higher level rogues, too, and not just to melee and caster classes.<br><br>Did I miss something in the last patch?  Is there any decent new player crafted gear out for us rogues?  <br><br>End Rant<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102208027151377></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102208027151377><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102208027151377>RE: Rant</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102208027151377#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121232><span id= >Fluxus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>132 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 22nd 11:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I usually don't have any trouble finding a group, but inevitably it WILL happen.&nbsp;&nbsp;People want a cleric or a tank or a chanter before a rogue.  Here's my solution.<br><br>Start your own group. ((I realize this is not always possible))<br><br>A few days ago, I couldn't get a group in Sol B.  So, I started one. First I grabbed a warrior.  then, I had 2 rogues ask if they could join... Heck yeah.. then finally picked up another warrior and a bard.  So, 3 rogues, 2 warriors and a bard began the slaughter.<br><br>Mobs dropped so fast that we NEVER had a need for a cleric.  The bard's regen song worked just fine.  Besides that, all three rogues and both warriors had EXCELLENT bind wound skill.  One of the warriors got Dotted and dropped down to 16 hitpoints when we started binding wounds.  It took about 15 seconds for us to bring him up to 50% health. (oh yeah... excellent suggestion on raising the BW skill for rogues to 75%!!!)<br><br>I had a group in Overthere once that consisted of 5 rogues and a shammy.  It was an absolute blood bath.  A battle that would've taken a minute in a 'normal' group took about 10 seconds... just long enough for ~10 backstabs to land ;-).<br><br>I like the safety net of having a cleric with CH or a good chanter with an AE Mez.  But, give me a group stacked with rogues any day.<br><br>And, just wanted to /agree with whomever made the comment about Rogue's getting more respect at higher levels... So true!  After 40th lvl people start to understand how much damage we actually do and will eagerly welcome us into their groups.  The next time you pop off a really nice backstab don't be shy about telling your group &quot;Ouch. 284 point backstab... that had to hurt.&quot;  They'll learn why rogues rule in no time.<br><br>And Slip, if you still have trouble finding a group, move on over to Tarew Marr and I'll group with ya anytime!  :-)<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br